cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a novel apprenticeship learning algorithm that uses batch data of observed expert behavior to learn an expert's underlying reward structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves the use of deep successor feature networks and transition-regularized imitation networks, which are techniques commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and control engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to a clinical task, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
